    <refnamediv>
        <refname>gl_LocalInvocationID</refname>
        <refpurpose>contains the index of work item currently being operated on by a compute shader</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv><title>Declaration</title>
        <funcsynopsis>
            <function>in uvec3 gl_LocalInvocationID</function>
        </funcsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsect1 id="description"><title>Description</title>
        <para>
            In the compute language, <function>gl_LocalInvocationID</function>
            is an input variable containing the n-dimensional index of the local
            work invocation within the work group that the current shader is
            executing in. The possible values for this variable range across
            the local work group size, i.e., (0,0,0) to (<function>gl_WorkGroupSize.x</function> - 1,
            <function>gl_WorkGroupSize.y</function> - 1, <function>gl_WorkGroupSize.z</function> - 1).
        </para>
    </refsect1>
